Performing testing on a fix to request checkin.  We currently have conditional code as follows in SSLCheckClass.java:

		if ((vendor.indexOf("Sun")) >= 0){
			// The following to use Sun JVM
			ctx = SSLContext.getInstance("TLS");
			kmf = KeyManagerFactory.getInstance("SunX509");
		}
		else{
			// or use the following for the IBM JVM
			ctx = SSLContext.getInstance("SSL");
			kmf = KeyManagerFactory.getInstance("IbmX509");
		}

This was due to fact that at the time the code was written, the same connection string would not work on both Sun and IBM for the SSLContext (in addition to the KeyManagerFactory difference).  Changing "SSL" to "TLS" or to "SSL_TLS" is working on the IBM 1.5 JVM without changing the default settings on IE 7 on Vista.  I will put together a request to fix.

